-- Solarpack Gets $66.4 Million for Three Chile Solar-Energy Plants
-- B y   S t e p h a n   N i e l s e n
-- 2013-07-30T14:41:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-30/solarpack-gets-66-4-million-for-three-chile-solar-energy-plants.html
Solarpack Corp. Tecnologica, the
Spanish solar-energy developer, will receive $66.4 million in
loans for three projects in  Chile ’s northern desert.  The financing comprises $41.4 million from the Inter-American Development Bank that was approved in March and a $25
million senior  loan  from  France ’s Proparco, Getxo, Spain-based
Solarpack said today in an e-mailed statement. Proparco is the
private investment unit of the French Development Agency.  The Pozo Almonte 2 and Pozo Almonte 3 plants will have
total capacity of 25.4 megawatts and are expected to begin
producing power in October, the Inter-American development Bank
said yesterday on its  website . The 1.1-megawatt Calama Solar 3
project went into operation in April 2012.  Astris Finance LLC advised Solarpack on the financing deal.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephan Nielsen in Sao Paulo at 
